<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Grumbles on 05-27-2002 04:32 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">/nod Ferrell

And even MGB has a pretty bad downside to it, it's a one shot deal- You can have 2+ clerics at a raid with MGB and Gaego and only one of them will do anything with it.

I would like to suggest (if by any chance Rich Waters see's this) move Marzin's Mark off of HP and put it on the same mobs that drop Gaego or one step down.  Instead of Doomshade, MM could be on the DM's etc.  Think about it, one of the biggest gripes that Druids have is that PotG is not wanted because you dont get the symbol buff component with it, and the difference between Naltron Mark and Marzin is pretty significant.  350ish hp's I think.  Been awhile since I played my cleric sorry, numbers a bit fuzzy.  And do you think any raid is going to sit around and wait for clerics to individually Marzin 20 some odd casters when in one whack they can all be Gaego'd and be done with it?  Not gonna happen.  

So why provide a solution to this class dispute on buff's and then stick the solution on a mob that 1% of players are going to get to?  Thats self defeating.  The object of spell and mob placement needs to be a balance of Risk vs Reward and class interoperability.  Are you trying to cause tension between Druids and Clerics?  I dont think VI is, but if not, then move the Marzin Mark spell so that it's a lot more accessible so that /GASP  it gets used and make a whole lot of players happy.  

Think about it...

MGB Cleric - Takes all the melee's off to a corner and Gaego's   :)
MGB Cleric - Takes all the casters off to a corner and MM's   :)
MGB Druid - Goes with the casters and PotG.  :)  

Everyone is happy!--
Druids got to use their MGB skill (finally)
Clerics got to use MGB (more than one per raid anyhow)
Casters all got a good symbol buff + Druid buff of uberness
Melee's got Gaego which is all they cared about in the first place.

How fricken hard is that????????????????



------------------
[URL=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18964]Grumbles[/URL]</TEXTAREA>
